---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TelemetryGrid from '@/components/telemetry/TelemetryGrid.astro';
import SectorBadge from '@/components/telemetry/SectorBadge.astro';

const updated = "2026-04-17";
---

<BaseLayout title="My Story">
  <nav class="paddock-override-nav">
    <a href="/" class="return-wall">← PIT WALL</a>
    <div class="nav-title">DRIVER BIOGRAPHY</div>
  </nav>

  <main class="story-viewport">
    <article class="paddock-article">
      
      <header class="recruiter-strip">
        <h1 class="driver-name">C M Nafi</h1>
        <p class="driver-subtitle">Solutions Engineer · Finance & Data Infrastructure</p>
        
        <div class="t-wrap">
          <TelemetryGrid 
            updated={updated}
            status="Open to conversations"
            stack="3+ years in institutional finance"
            link="#"
            linkLabel="US Citizen / Green Card"
          />
        </div>
        
        <div class="filter-chips">
          <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank" class="chip">DOWNLOAD RÉSUMÉ → PDF</a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cm-nafi/" target="_blank" class="chip">LINKEDIN ↗</a>
          <a href="mailto:nafi@cmnafi.com" class="chip">EMAIL</a>
          <a href="#" class="chip">BOOK 20 MIN ↗</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p1" label="THE SHORT ANSWER" /></div>
          <p>I'm a solutions engineer at Dasseti, working at the intersection of institutional capital and the data infrastructure that moves it. I grew up in Bangladesh, left home at sixteen on a full scholarship to a United World College in China, and landed in a town of eight thousand in Iowa for university. I've since worked with BlackRock, Mayo Clinic, and SkyBridge Capital — three very different institutions that share a single truth: the answer is almost always in the data, and the edge is almost always in how quickly you can get to it. I build tools, I ship writing, and I try to keep the feedback loop short.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p2" label="QUALIFYING ROUND" /></div>
          <h3>Bangladesh → China → Iowa → Tampa</h3>
          <p>I grew up in <strong>Dinajpur, Bangladesh</strong>, in a household that treated reading as the default answer to boredom. At sixteen I left on a full scholarship to <strong>UWC Changshu (China)</strong>, moving to a country where I didn't speak the language and learning most of what I know about self-reliance in the space of two years.</p>
          <p>University took me to <strong>Luther College in Decorah, Iowa</strong> — a town of eight thousand people where winter teaches you patience and a small campus teaches you that depth beats breadth if you let it. I majored in <strong>Data Science</strong> and minored in <strong>Computer Science</strong>, and graduated <strong>2022</strong>.</p>
          <p>I now live in <strong>Tampa, Florida</strong>, which is where the F1, the cricket, and the work all happen to sit.</p>
          <blockquote><strong>What the route gave me:</strong> the instinct to read a system top-down and bottom-up at the same time, comfort with being the newest person in the room, and a bias for building the tool I wish existed instead of complaining about the one that doesn't.</blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section career-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p3" label="THE RACE" /></div>
          
          <div class="brew-card stint-card">
            <div class="brew-meta">
              <span class="brew-accent badge-project">DASSETI</span>
              <span class="brew-date">2023 – Present · Remote / Tampa, FL</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Solutions Engineer</h3>
            <p>A data platform used by institutional allocators to run due diligence on asset managers. I sit between product, engineering, and the allocators themselves — turning what a client needs into what the platform does.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Onboard institutional clients onto the DDQ platform and shape the data pipeline that feeds their manager-monitoring workflows.</li>
              <li>Build integrations against SEC EDGAR, Form ADV, and third-party data providers.</li>
              <li>Partner with engineering on features that started as client-specific and graduated into the core product.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Every feature I ship saves an analyst somewhere a week of manual spreadsheet work.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="brew-card stint-card">
            <div class="brew-meta">
              <span class="brew-accent badge-note">SKYBRIDGE CAPITAL</span>
              <span class="brew-date">2021 – 2022 · New York, NY</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Data Analyst</h3>
            <p>A multi-strategy alternative investment firm. Exposure to fund-of-funds construction, manager selection, and the operational side of allocating capital at institutional scale.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Supported the manager-selection team with quantitative screening models across 200+ hedge fund profiles.</li>
              <li>Built internal dashboards tracking exposure by strategy, geography, and liquidity profile.</li>
              <li>Contributed to investment memos for alternative mandates.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="brew-card stint-card">
            <div class="brew-meta">
              <span class="brew-accent badge-note">MAYO CLINIC</span>
              <span class="brew-date">2021 – 2022 · Rochester, MN</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Data Engineer</h3>
            <p>A healthcare institution where the data engineering is operating at a scale most fintechs never see. The lesson was that reliability beats cleverness, and that messy real-world data is the job, not an obstacle to the job.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Engineered ETL pipelines against clinical data sets serving research teams.</li>
              <li>Owned and automated reporting pipelines handling high-velocity data.</li>
              <li>Partnered with clinical stakeholders to translate ambiguous questions into measurable outputs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="brew-card stint-card">
            <div class="brew-meta">
              <span class="brew-accent badge-note">BLACKROCK</span>
              <span class="brew-date">2022 – 2023 · NYC</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Data Analyst</h3>
            <p>The world's largest asset manager. The first place I learned that a trillion dollars is a spreadsheet problem, a risk problem, and a storytelling problem all at once.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Analytics team, working on risk reporting and fund performance metrics.</li>
              <li>Built dashboards mapping capital flow analytics to strategy performance.</li>
              <li>Presented findings to senior stakeholders at the end of the program.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p1" label="CURRENT LAP" /></div>
          <p>Day job is Dasseti. Outside that, I'm building a set of <strong>public finance data tools</strong> at <a href="/garage">cmnafi.com/garage</a> — most notably the ADV Screener, a 13F Data Finder, and a manager intelligence dashboard that ties entity resolution, regulatory filings, and narrative summarization together. They're works in progress on purpose.</p>
          <p>I also write <strong>one or two Field Notes a week</strong> on <a href="/field-notes">cmnafi.com/field-notes</a> covering the corners of institutional finance, venture capital, and market structure that I find most worth explaining. The writing and the tools feed each other — every post surfaces something worth turning into a tool, and every tool surfaces something worth writing about.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section telemetry-grid-stint">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p2" label="THE SPECS" /></div>
          <div class="spec-grid">
            <div class="spec-col">
              <h4>Languages & frameworks</h4>
              <p>TypeScript · Python · SQL · Astro · Next.js · React · MDX</p>
              <h4>Data & infra</h4>
              <p>PostgreSQL · pgvector · Supabase · Pandas · REST/GraphQL APIs · SEC EDGAR</p>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-col">
              <h4>AI & tooling</h4>
              <p>OpenAI / Anthropic APIs · Claude Code + gstack · embeddings and hybrid search · agent workflows</p>
              <h4>Domains</h4>
              <p>Institutional asset management · hedge funds & alternatives · regulatory data (Form ADV, 13F) · due-diligence workflows · capital markets · sports finance and private equity.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-col">
              <h4>How I work</h4>
              <p>Bias to ship · one pager before a system · short feedback loops · writing is thinking · small tools over big platforms · tests the moment a bug appears, not before.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="p3" label="EDUCATION" /></div>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Luther College</strong>, Decorah, Iowa · B.A. in Data Science, Computer Science minor, 2022.</li>
            <li><strong>UWC Changshu, China</strong> · IB Diploma. Full merit scholarship.</li>
          </ul>
          <h4 class="cert-title">Key Certifications</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>IBM: Introduction to Data Engineering</li>
            <li>Google: Data Analytics Professional Certificate</li>
            <li>DeepLearning.AI: Neural Networks and Deep Learning</li>
            <li>Salesforce: Einstein Analytics</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="sector1" label="THE PADDOCK" /></div>
          <p>I play <strong>competitive cricket</strong> on the weekends — currently turning out for <strong>Tampa Bengals</strong> in the Tampa league. Five-wicket hauls and narrow chases show up on the blog with surprising regularity.</p>
          <p>I follow <strong>Formula 1</strong> the way some people follow theology — I can tell you which team's pit wall is worth listening to on radio and which corner at Suzuka decides a season. I read a book a month, mostly non-fiction, and occasionally a novel that makes me feel underprepared.</p>
          <p>If we ever talk, there's a non-trivial chance it drifts into one of these.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="story-section">
          <div class="section-badge"><SectorBadge variant="sector2" label="PIT BOX" /></div>
          <ul class="contact-list">
            <li>✉️ <strong>Email</strong> — <a href="mailto:nafi@cmnafi.com">nafi@cmnafi.com</a> · replies within two business days.</li>
            <li>💼 <strong>LinkedIn</strong> — <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cm-nafi/" target="_blank">linkedin.com/in/cm-nafi</a></li>
            <li>💻 <strong>GitHub</strong> — <a href="https://github.com/CMNafi" target="_blank">github.com/CMNafi</a></li>
            <li>📅 <strong>20-minute intro call</strong> — <a href="#">Book Meeting</a></li>
          </ul>
          <br/>
          <p><strong>I'm most useful in conversations about:</strong> institutional finance data infrastructure, tools for allocators and due-diligence teams, solutions engineering at finance-adjacent SaaS, and technical writing for finance audiences.</p>
          <p><strong>I'm probably not your person for:</strong> sell-side equity research roles, pure quant trading seats, or anything that requires me to stop building things to run a long sales cycle.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .paddock-override-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 2rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .return-wall { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .nav-title { color: var(--pitlane-white); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; }
  
  .story-viewport { min-height: 100vh; background: var(--paddock-black); }
  .paddock-article { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 2rem 6rem; }
  
  .recruiter-strip {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--carbon);
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  .driver-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--pitlane-white);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .driver-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .t-wrap { max-width: 700px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }

  /* CHIPS */
  .filter-chips {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .chip {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 11px;
    border: 1px solid var(--graphite);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: 0.2s;
  }
  .chip:hover {
    background: var(--pitlane-white);
    color: var(--paddock-black);
    border-color: var(--pitlane-white);
  }

  /* STORY SECTIONS */
  .prose { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .story-section { margin-bottom: 5rem; }
  .section-badge { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  
  .prose h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--pitlane-white); }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(244, 244, 241, 0.85); }
  .prose strong { color: var(--pitlane-white); }
  .prose a { color: var(--telemetry-green); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: rgba(0, 230, 118, 0.4); text-underline-offset: 4px; transition: 0.2s; }
  .prose a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--telemetry-green); }
  .prose blockquote { border-left: 3px solid var(--warning-amber); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-left: 0; font-style: italic; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); }
  
  /* STINT CARDS (Garage style) */
  .brew-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--carbon);
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--graphite);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .brew-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .brew-accent { padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 2px; }
  .badge-project { background: rgba(0, 230, 118, 0.1); color: var(--telemetry-green); }
  .badge-note { background: rgba(139, 145, 154, 0.1); color: var(--muted); }
  .brew-date { color: var(--muted); }

  .brew-card h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--pitlane-white); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; }
  .brew-card p { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(244, 244, 241, 0.7); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .brew-card ul { margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .brew-card li { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(244, 244, 241, 0.8); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  /* GRID FOR SPECS */
  .spec-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .spec-col h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--graphite);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .spec-col p { font-size: 1rem; }

  /* LISTS */
  .prose ul.contact-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .prose ul.contact-list li { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .cert-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  @media print {
    .paddock-override-nav, .filter-chips { display: none !important; }
    .story-viewport { background: #fff; color: #000; }
    .prose a { color: #000; text-decoration: none; }
  }
</style>
